-- BT appoints former HSBC executive Joe Garner to lead Openreach 
-- By Paul Sandle
-- Mon Jan 13, 2014 09:36AM EST
-- None



LONDON, Jan 13 (Reuters) - BT <BT.L> said it appointed former HSBC <HSBA.L> executive Joe Garner to lead Openreach, its local networks unit that is rolling out super-fast broadband in Britain.

Garner, who joins in mid-February, replaces Liv Garfield, who is leaving the telecoms company to become chief executive of utility Severn Trent <SVT.L>. [ID:nL5N0J31MS]